physical_examinations.relevant_findings: The patient displayed normal spontaneous movements, appropriate responses to painful stimuli, and a right-sided inversion deformity; mildly weak dorsiflexion and plantar flexion of the foot and toes; mild atrophy of both legs; and absence of the anal reflex.
Imaging showed posterior fusion defects at T9–11, L4–5, and S-1, partial sacral agenesis, costal abnormalities, and mild triventricular hydrocephalus.
The patient underwent preoperative craniospinal MR imaging for evaluation of myelomeningocele and associated split cord malformation.
